[1] Undiagnosed gastroenteritis - Australia (Tasmania)
Date: Tue 31 Aug 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez, M.D.<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: ABC News, Australia, Tue 31 Aug 2004 [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200408/s1188566.htm>

Australia: Gastroenteritis Cases Hospitalized in Hobart (Tasmania)
--------------------------------------------------
A number of patients have been admitted to the Royal Hobart Hospital with
gastroenteritis. 7 patients have been admitted to a 10-bed isolation area
within a medical ward of the hospital. A spokeswoman says the isolation
area is standard procedure for such outbreaks. She stated that the patients
are being treated according to infection control standards to minimise
further cases.
The spokeswoman says no other patients have been treated at the hospital at
this stage and the Director of Public Health is not aware of a wider public
outbreak of gastroenteritis. She says the extra patients have not had an
effect on elective surgery at the hospital.
